# Charge conjugate definitions that are very .dec specific:
# 1) Specific to decay files
# 2) Special, non-standard particles, hence not in the PDG data tables
# 3) "Particles" defined at the quark level, for Pythia model decays
#
# For all these special cases, use 'ChargeConj' statements to instruct
# and help the parser, so that charge-conjugate decays can be dealt with.


# Particles specific to decay files
# ---------------------------------
ChargeConj  anti-c-hadron  c-hadron
ChargeConj  anti-rndmflav  rndmflav
ChargeConj  specflav       specflav

# Particles not yet in the PDG data tables
# ----------------------------------------
ChargeConj  anti-N(2090)-  N(2090)+
ChargeConj  anti-N(2090)0  N(2090)0

ChargeConj  B_s10  anti-B_s10


